HEADWORD: Pageantry
<hw>Pag"eant*ry</hw> <pr>(-r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Scenic shows
or spectacles, taken collectively; spectacular quality;
splendor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such <qex>pageantry</qex> be to the people shown.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>pageantry</qex> of festival.</q> <rj><qau>J. A.
Symonds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Pomp; parade; show; display; spectacle.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>page boy</ent>⟦br⟧
